            "client": "website",
            "content": "<p>How do people (especially poly folks, but curious to hear from everyone) about what information to share with their partners? I've been thinking about this a bunch lately, since I feel like I inherited this expectation from popular culture/the media/the communities that I grew up in that it's expected that it's ok to share everything with your partner, even things that aren't relevant to your relationship with your partner.</p>\n<p>On thinking about this more, I don't really know how to approach it - on the one hand, it's nice to have a person or people you can go to when something happens that you don't necessarily need support about, but you feel a desire to share with someone. On the other hand, if that thing is \"I had a conversation with $person where we talked about $thing\" (and $thing is somewhat private), that seems not good (since $thing should be, by default, between you and $person).</p>\n<p>How do people balance this? I guess I could explicitly reach out to people and check before sharing things, but that seems pretty heavyweight and possibly awkward. I've been increasingly leaning towards not sharing things, since that feels right to me, but I'm curious what other folks think :)</p>",
            "content_type": "text/html",
