            "client": "website",
            "content": "<p>I do think that it is reasonable, and tend to myself, to not share information about partners between them unless there is some explicit reason to. It seems like a really good way to encourage drama and all sorts of weird interactions and questions.</p>\n<p>Part of the trickiness is that even though the information <em>itself</em> is harmless, the metainformation (who knows about it, who knows who knows about it, the timing for who knows about who knows about it) can make people grumpy. \"Why did you talk to him about it before me?\" \"Do you know how she knew to ask her about it?\" etc.</p>\n<p>Combine this with the often...fluid...nature of non-monogamous relationships and it's just an opsec nightmare.</p>",
