            "client": "website",
            "content": "<p>I'm starting a new job, and I'm trying to figure out how to handle this delicately. Not being out as poly at my last job made me feel uncomfortable. A fairly common interaction was a friend asking about my weekend, followed by me responding, \"I'm seeing my... uh... friend...\" However, there is still some stigma around the lifestyle, so I don't want to out myself as a slut, if that's how it'll read.</p>\n<p>If I shouldn't be out as poly, which partner is \"partner\" in my conversations, and which is/are \"friend\"? Do any of y'all have advice?</p>",
