        {
            "avatar_url": "https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/c97a0d7ab8eb6034a735e9788ecc8af9?d=identicon&version=1",
            "client": "ZulipMobile",
            "content": "<p>I think there are two aspects of this -- is it something that the general company environment is ok with (e.g. are there other poly people who are out at work?), and how do you feel about dealing with the reactions of anybody who's going to react to it. Like so many norms in software vs the rest of the world, I think at most software shops, coming out as poly would be totally fine with the company culture. Google has an unofficial poly mailing list, even. (Google has a lot of things, though.) So mostly it's about whether you expect the people you work directly with to be cool about it, I guess. So probably worth getting to know them first?</p>",
