            "client": "website",
            "content": "<blockquote>\n<p>What things have helped you make decisions like this?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>After an embarrassing time in my school years trying to help with sort of thing, I've settled on a policy of \"if you're talking to me about breaking up, I'll offer you fondest wishes and support you but politely tell you to figure it out.\" They have access to information and context you can't hope to, your own feelings about them as a friend or potential partner will invariably bias your advice, and overall it's just a Whole Thing.</p>\n<p>Unless they are literally posing a \"I am in imminent danger due to this abusive relationship\" or \"I would like to enter into a relationship with you this very instant but for some contrived reason I can't do that until this breakup goes through\" there isn't really an upside to getting involved in drama that isn't your own. Set boundaries.</p>\n<p>Besides, they're probably  gonna follow what their heart says anyways so advice is at best you're wasting your time and at worst they'll either hold you accountable for the outcomes of their own decisions or continue bothering you as they fail to apply your advice in the way you intended.</p>",
