            "content": "<p>I don't mean to be glib here, but I think the poly rule of thumb is \"don't date siblings, roommates, or good friends\".  You can date either one, but not both, esp at the same time.  K has seen this first-hand and has developed some wisdom around it, which is why she's forcing the exclusive-or with C before it blows up (she still has to deal with C as a roommate even after you and K or you and C break up).  It seems counterintuitive to new poly folk; aren't we poly so we can get away from attachment drama?  But the answer is no, you can never get away from attachment drama when being intimate with humans.</p>",
