            "content": "<p>It seems like you're having to regulate/lie on behalf of K. They want you to do work to maintain some relationship between them and C by not mentioning a restriction they also want you to honor...that doesn't seem to me to be reasonable.</p>\n<p>In your position, I'd tell K that I'd be happy not to pursue things with C but that I wasn't going to lie about why. If C asks, answer. If C doesn't ask, it will be to them One of Life's Great Mysteries. </p>\n<p>If it turns out that honoring K's request meant that you missed out on a great thing with C, or that telling C why you were giving them space caused trouble with K and then K took it out on you...well, I'd chalk that up to the assorted bullshit that sometimes happens with poly.</p>\n<p>There are always more people out there--that's kinda one of the big selling points of poly.</p>\n<p>Good luck either way--you deserve to have low-stress fulfilling relationship! :) <img alt=\":hug:\" class=\"emoji\" src=\"https://zulip-avatars.s3.amazonaws.com/13/emoji/images/58.png\" title=\"hug\"></p>",
