            "client": "website",
            "content": "<p>The theory of the book <a href=\"https://www.goodreads.com/en/book/show/520311\" title=\"https://www.goodreads.com/en/book/show/520311\">The Two Step</a>, is that in relationships with anxious-avoidant dynamics, what is important is having a concept of \"mean regression\". As in, intimacy is found in the spaces where people switch their typical roles (the \"anxious\" goes to do something else with their life and stops pursuing, the \"avoidant\" pursues the \"anxious\"). Relationships that have \"longevity\" will have a dance that more or less revolves around that mean.</p>",
